images.description:
Update 3:  under no circumstances do I actually give my dog chocolate covered chicken wings.  But I do make wildly esoteric and ill timed jokes that fail to land.  

Update two:  she is home and happy.  Maybe a UTI or a mild injury.  Thanks to everyone for keeping me company and sending pika love.  Imgur is my favorite place on earth because of you good people. 

https://imgur.com/gallery/9UZ4XFH

Update:  so it seems like she is fine?  They are running one last blood and kidney test and otherwise found just a little bit of UT inflammation.  Ill never err on the side of not worrying, especially when I see blood, but it seems like she should be ok.  Probably just needs some anti inflammatory meds and a check up in a week.  My dad drove an hour to come sit with me while I waited to hear from the vet.  We went to the bar and had some drinks and wings.  I didnt save one for Pika.  She only likes them dipped in chocolate anyway.  

This is probably the wrong meme format and I dont want to hear about it.  This is how I feel.  Shes my best and only friend.  Shes my therapy animal and she was peeing blood this morning.  At first I thought she was marking over someones spilled red drink so I took her for  another short walk and sure enough, 10 steps later she made a little marking spot bright red in the snow.  Her first peep was healthy, but Im really worried this had been going on for a while and I didnt notice until now because it only just began snowing.  I dont think Ill make it with out her.  I cant afford her vet bills and my dad keeps letting me put them on his credit card.  It makes me feel so utterly useless that I cant afford her health bills.  I broke down completely when the vet asked if I wanted them ti resuscitate if her heart stopped.  I personally wouldnt want to be.  I have even considered getting DNR tattooed over my chest to be sure.  Honestly the only reason I dont is because I worry what would happen to Pika if I were dead.  

Imgurians, if you read this far thanks.  Im not asking for any kind of money, like I said, Daddy is covering his looser son.  But could you send me some love in comments?  Im really really scared.  I dont have any close friends here and Im so so scared.

Flintlock sporting rifle from the collection of George IV at Carlton House, London. The gun has a single blued steel barrel of octagonal and twisted heart shaped cross section inlaid in gold at the backsight Walster A Saarbruck. The lock signed Walster A Saarbruck and engraved with a cherub offering a bird to a retriever dog and also chiselled with flowers and trophies against a gold ground. Walnut wood half-stock with horn fore-end cap and twisted horn tipped wooden ramrod. The stock carved with rococo scrolls, a sea monsters head and griffin, the butt decorated with inlaid silver wire work.The silver wire decoration on the butt is taken directly from De Lacollombe, Nouveaux desseins D'Arquebuseries Dessine Grave par De Lacollombe a Paris 1730. Se Vend Chez De Marteau Eleve De Feu Mr De Lacollombe.

This is a gunsmiths tour de force where ingenuity and craftsmanship are added on top of rich decoration. All the external screws are concealed so the gun cannot be disassembled without knowing how to release a secret hidden catch to start the process. The barrel is part twisted to form a heart shape which acts as rifling as well as being designed to impress. Guns with unusual bore shapes were made as curiosities and demonstrations in the art of gunsmithing rather than for their accuracy in shooting.

Overall length 42.5 in. Barrel length  27.25 in. Bore (between grooves) 1/2 in.

Provenance
The Carlton House Arms Catalogue, no. 749 notes that This curious twisted barrel gun was made at Saabruck in Germany it discharges a ball in the shape of a heart, a well finished gun.

Samfaina: https://www.rct.uk/collection/61100/flintlock-sporting-rifle-pirschbuumlchse

data.title: I'd make a title, but I'm already on my 5th hobby today.

images.description:
Today I started taking Vyvanse (generic I think). It's the first time I've taken any medication for ADHD since I was in the 6th grade. Originally I started on Ritalin, but my mom switched me to Adderall when I was in the 6th grade. Ritalin sucked, it made me zombie out and I was basically a husk in a chair. Adderall was even worse, it made me pull out my hair and sort it in a pile. They called it a tick. They changed my dosage and I started having panic attacks and it raised my heart rate. After that I stopped taking medication altogether. 

Now I'm 31 years old, my job is picking up, I need to focus on certs, I own a home that I need to maintain, I have a girlfriend and pets, and I've been getting a stronger sense of wanting to make something for years now. All of this has been piling up against me and making me feel like I don't have time to do anything at all, so what do I do? I sit around wasting time not doing anything.

Well after at least 5 years of telling myself I need to see a doctor. I finally managed to push myself to do it. It took a bit longer than I was expecting because wait times for mental care doctors are ridiculous. A month for the psychiatric doctor, and then another month just to talk to a doctor for the prescription.

I really wanted to try Azstarys, I've heard great things about it, but it's not covered by a lot of insurance companies yet. I read from a lot of experiences that Vyvanse was similar, so that's what I'm trying first. I got the prescription yesterday and started it today. 

It took some time to take effect, but I started noticing a buzzing feeling in my head. Not long after that, I decided I would start working on some studying while waiting for work to pick up. I've gotten certs for work before, but lately any time I look at a screen to study, my brain would scream at me and I couldn't focus on anything. If you've ever watched Babadook (great movie) and remember the scene with the kid screaming in the car? That's my brain. WHY CANT YOU JUST BE NORMAL?!

Now my brain is basically throwing a green light at me telling me to go. It's only been one day, but it's been a good experience so far. I'm hoping it pans out and I can really rely on it to help with more than just work.

As a side note, it's not perfect by any means. I was quick to realize that my ability to focus or get side tracked are relatively the same. It's definitely a tool to help with my problems, and not a cure all solution. It's just easier to get back on the issue at hand.

tl;dr I'm finally working to tackle my problems with ADHD.
Good recovery tho

images.description:
Well, I have good news and bad news. 

The good news is, no cancer spread to my lymph nodes or outside of my uterus. 

The bad news is I will have to have a hysterectomy to fully beat this. Its scheduled for November 30th. 

Im doing this in a mini meme dump to attempt to distance myself from bad news.

I was informed I had to take about a month after to recover, which is a huge hit for me. the psychological impact of literally being gaslit by the medical system while my body developed cancer has done a number on me as well, I have to admit it. This has been in the works for years and I was dismissed so many times with cramps.

Regardless, everything is going to be okay. Thank you so much to everyone who has donated so far, and please dont feel obligated to contribute again - your support is already appreciated beyond belief. 

Anything helps, even just a share and a kind word.

I set up on PayPal and gofundme, since folks seem to be more comfortable with one or the other. This is lame and Im uncomfortable asking for help, thank you all for bearing with me.

images.description:
Let my heart beat in the chest of someone who actually wants to be here

Wow, I honestly thought this would die in usersub.  I guess I need to be a bit more detailed as some of you (a very small amount) don't seem to catch what I was laying down.

Most suicides do not result in the successful harvesting of organs.  Which seems such a waste when there are so many in desperate need.  

If there were a system, methodology, practice or program that allowed for medically assisted death (I truly despise the word suicide and all of the lore associated with it) we could perhaps find a way to improve the lives of others.

To the one who is rigidly upset with my take, your solution has the acidic ring of "have you tried being happy".  

Everyone seems to always focus on the impact such a choice has on those around the one who makes the choice.  But where is the compassion for the person struggling?  I often wonder if it is understood just how difficult it is on the one making the choice. 

The conversation around chosen death truly needs to change, this 'it's selfish' mindset is also very selfish to the one thinking it.  Not everyone is built for life and asking them to plaster a smile and suffer through so that you don't have to realize the hurt of their absence is rather odd to me.

and one last thing.  Don't compare traumas.  That's some idiotic simplification.  What is survivable to one is not a good measure of how bad something is for another.

anywho, thanks to all of you who got the gist.  Maybe one day we can get to a point where we can discuss this kind of stuff.

images.description: Not gonna lie, I was pretty bummed out after finding out that Imgur is significantly limiting the "international" gift exchange when I wanted to sign up for Secret Santa on Wednesday. I have been participating for two years now and both Secret Santa events I got to take part in were the highlights of my holiday seasons despite not receiving anything last year. I am from Europe and I move around a lot. I have lots of friends and family from other EU countries. Part of what made Secret Santa so amazing these last two years is that both my gifter and my giftees came from really distant countries and cultures and I got to experience something I normally wouldn't. It just isn't the same if I know I am going to get matched with someone from my relative vicinity, whose culture I may be very familiar with. It's even worse for Americans who are, if I understood well, basically limited to exchanging gifts with Canadians if they choose the international option, which is kinda against the point. I understand Imgur's reasoning and appreciate that they are trying to make the event better, but my country's post has a flat rate for ALL international packages. So regardless of whether I am sending a gift 100 kilometers away or to the other end of the earth, it will cost me exactly the same. So why not make it more exciting?

So I thought to myself, fuck it, why don't I just try doing it like this? I am asking if anyone wants to match with me privately and do an intercontinental gift exchange? :) I have been on Imgur for a very long time and the badges on my profile prove I have sent a gift for both Secret Santa exchanges I was part of. The only thing I require is that the other person can also prove they have successfully participated in Secret Santa before.

Hell, if there's more of y'all who would be interested in this and if it would be fine with all of you, I'd be open to making a group where a number of us could get matched anonymously and send/receive a gift from another continent. I don't blame Imgur for their decision, it's understandable, but also makes Secret Santa lose its charm for some of us so that makes me open to giving something like this a shot! If you are interested, feel free to DM me or comment.

EDIT: Wow, most viral! I didn't expect this post to get this much traction! Lots of people, at least 12 for now, have expressed interest in this so I DM'd everyone to see if they are okay with making a little group exchange together! I will be keeping an eye on all the comments in the coming days so whoever is interested can comment or DM me and I will count them in too. If I missed your comment, feel free to DM me. Since it looks like we might have a little group exchange, sadly I will have to limit the exchange to only those users who have a badge on their profile which verifies they have sent a gift on one of the past exchanges. I hope nobody takes this personally. Unfortunately, many people have negative experiences with past exchanges where they put a lot of effort in their gift and got nothing in return and the only certain method of reducing the number of potential disappointments is limiting the exchange to people I can verify have sent gifts in the exchange before. Also don't forget that Imgur's official Secret Santa is open to everyone!

images.description: Saw this PBF comic. It immediately made me think of when I worked at an inpatient pediatric psych facility. We'd get these kids who just needed some structure and calm. They'd almost immediately behave like any other kid and we'd wonder why they were even there. Then we'd meet the parents. The parents would make no effort to change themselves or the environment. The kids would leave us, and be right back the following week. Lather, rinse, repeat. I had to leave the field after 4 years because I just couldn't emotionally separate work and life.

I get it work must be done but I have noise cancelling earbuds and on top of those noise cancelling headphones and I can still hear them.

The layout is complexes stacked on other complexes. Managed by the HOA but individually owned. The HOA hired contractors to redo some of the old decks. Landlords and owners didn't have a say.

We woke up and it smelled so bad I couldn't breathe and my eyes hurt. But HOA don't care tehe they basically tell us to suck it up, multiple units are getting their decks rebuilt. 

I feel like I'm over reacting and should just deal with it.

Ignore the crappy video just wanted to show how loud it is. You can hear things falling off the walls in the background.

I still get really bad anxiety with loud noises because we left our last apartment due to pile driving right next to our window (for 10 months) and an apartment complex that also told us they don't care.

Here's some fun videos I took if you don't know what a pile driver sounds like (120db): https://i.imgur.com/BmgrZV4.mp4

https://imgur.com/gallery/OaBfhLz

For reference: "EnShitification" refers to how it's becoming more difficult to return the "results you want", and companies instead throw crap at you you don't want(and ads). Tweaking their algorithms to maximize interaction, ad revenue, clicks, etc. 
Profit. Even IF you're paying for the service.

It used to be that a particular search for a partner would return no results.
It was the universe's way of saying "there's no perfect dream partner for you, idjit" and "stop trying to find a 25yo athletic millionaire, of this EXACT specified height" - they either don't exist, or have already found a partner by other means.

But now.

It's the damn opposite.
"Here's everyone in the world of your age range"

Religion/denomination?
Height? Body type?
Smoker? Tee-totaler/heavy drinker?
Marital status?
Wanting children? Already having children?
Relationship sought?
Education?

Hell no! We don't care about that!

Sure, we'll let you SET your search criteria/preferences. 

BUT WE'LL COMPLETELY IGNORE ALL OF IT!

I can't find a match, because I have to wade through an ocean of incompatible people. You'll have to look at every single one.

Oh... And we'll also take away your ability to "favourite" someone you might like, and want to come back to later. Communicate right this minute, or you'll never be able to find them again.

It's not like it's impossible, or even difficult, too search the OPTIONS THAT THEY LET YOU SELECT, for both you, and the one you seek... Because they used to do it. 

For a little while, in between then and now, they would still use the height criteria. But then got rid of that too.

Another site I used to be on would let you prioritize which were "makes or break", and which you were more flexible on.

But no.
Lol - "We don't actually want you to find someone! Cause then you'll stop paying us!"
"Besides - when you spend hours ploughing through the plethora of potential partners, that increases our interaction and engagement metrics!"

Damnit, it's frustrating.

I'm strongly considering paying a good coder to help me crawl their database. You don't want to limit the results? I'll set up a mirror sequel db and do it my damn self!

Just got to rate limit & randomize the queries, so my account doesn't get banned.

TOS? Fuck TOS? I just want to find my "forever person"!

FP edit: Wow. Way more popular than expecting.
Maybe it resonates with existing feelings of y'all?
It's ChristianMingle, btw, but other are similar. 

The number of Anti-COVID-Vaxxers, and wierd right wingers isn't crazy high, but not infrequent either. They usually go straight to my block list.

If there's any chance this finds it's way to a "moderate-to-hard-left" Christian gal, who hasn't found her other half yet... drop me a line?

data.title: Being in my 30s and knowing this hurts

images.description:
Next year is my 20 year highschool reunion. I am finally in a place where I can go back to college. This summer was shaping up to be pivotal for our (My wife and I) future after the kids move out. My trip to school is a short one and buying a second vehicle seemed frivolous. Instead we decide a small 49cc scooter would be a better value. We find a cute little blue Chinese scooter for $1800. Which was everything we had but being able to own it outright seemed right at the time. Leaving the store we use our insurance app to attempt to add the scooter, unfortunately Can't seem to locate any information and see a note on the app stating we have 30 days to register a new vehicle. With the confidence of this, off I scooted.
This was Saturday August..5th I believe.. Sunday, the very next day I decided to ride the scooter across town to pick up some proper riding gear. At this point I only own a good helmet. While riding under an overpass, a truck merged into my lane knocking me off my scooter. I suffered a broken ankle, 7 broken ribs, broken shoulder, torn labrum and a pretty serious concussion. Honestly the road rash was the least of my concerns. Truck fled the scene and despite an officer witnessing the end of my crash, he claimed to not see any other vehicle involved. Insurance was quick to say they were paying for nothing because my scooter is not a vehicle in their eyes. There is no help available that I have been able to find in either suing my insurance or tracking down the truck. I posted in local watch groups asking for help, and a local attorney said I had no case.  As time has passed my shoulder has required major surgery to repair and I am having lingering effects from the concussion. Attempts to focus on classwork have led me to massive panic attacks, just had one writing this. My wife is struggling to keep the house afloat with me being essentially bedridden for two months. To do this, she is working full-time, attending online school, cooking dinner every night for four people and making sure our two teenage kids make it to and from school and activities. My kids are smart but not exactly helpful around the house so it's been hard for me to watch her be stretched so thin. 

Not sure what's next, physical therapy and I guess a reassess of my future.  After being homeless in 2019, I've been through worse and I know complaining isn't going to help, but goddamn this one hurts.
Thanks for a place to vent.
